  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with typical clinical manifestations of Lyme neuroborreliosis and intrathecal
             antibody production against Borrelia burgdorferi

          -  patients with typical clinical manifestations of Lyme neuroborreliosis and erythema
             migrans within three months

          -  patients with some clinical manifestations of Lyme neuroborreliosis and presence of
             antibodies against Borrelia burgdorferi bacteria in blood.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnancy

          -  lactation

          -  use of any antibiotics two weeks before study treatments begins

          -  an allergy to ceftriaxone or doxycycline
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
